WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.834
Myocarditis predominantly affects young adults, with a

00:00:02.834 --> 00:00:04.049
3-to-1 male predominance.

00:00:04.049 --> 00:00:06.883
Epidemiologic studies suggest it underlies 9 to

00:00:06.883 --> 00:00:09.717
16 percent of sudden cardiac death cases

00:00:09.717 --> 00:00:11.337
in individuals under 35.

00:00:11.337 --> 00:00:14.171
Pathophysiology follows three phases: an initial viral

00:00:14.171 --> 00:00:17.005
entry and direct myocyte injury phase lasting

00:00:17.005 --> 00:00:19.839
one to three days; an innate and

00:00:19.839 --> 00:00:22.673
adaptive immune activation phase from days 3

00:00:22.673 --> 00:00:25.507
through 14, characterized by T-cell infiltration and

00:00:25.507 --> 00:00:28.341
cytokine release; and a chronic fibrotic remodeling

00:00:28.341 --> 00:00:31.176
phase if the inflammatory insult is not

00:00:31.176 --> 00:00:33.200
resolved, predisposing to dilated cardiomyopathy.
